<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>81<percent/> of 75</li> 
<li>20<percent/> of 234</li> 
<li>5<percent/> of 2328</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>C: 5<percent/> of 2328</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{81}\%\cdot{75}={60.75}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{20}\%\cdot{234}={46.8}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}\%\cdot{2328}={116.4}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 5<percent/> of 2328 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

